[1]
Date: 22 Dec 2004
From: Chris Griot <Christian.Griot@ivi.admin.ch>
Source: Yahoo News [edited]
<http://asia.news.yahoo.com/041222/4/1tjl0.html>

[ProMED-mail would like to thank Akira Goto <dolphin@mail.ne.jp> for
submitting similar information. - Mod.MPP]

Suspected Weak Bird Influenza Shows up in S.Korea: Ministry
--------------------------------
A suspected case of the milder bird flu virus has been found at a duck farm
in Gwangju, the Ministry of Agriculture and Forestry said Wednesday
The H5N2 strain of avian influenza is less virulent than the H5N1 strain
that swept through South Korea and Southeast Asia in 2003.
The ministry said that it has destroyed and buried the ducks in the farm in
question and have set up tougher quarantine inspections in Gwangju.
The strain is said to pose no health threat to humans.
"The H5N2-strain has never spread to humans and must be differentiated from
the deadly bird flu that spread through Asia last year," a official said.
--
