Source: The Korea Times [edited]
<http://times.hankooki.com/lpage/nation/200412/kt2004120917530610510.htm>

Nation Alert Over Animal Epidemics
Quarantine Strengthened to Prevent Recurrence of Bird Flu
------------------------
Quarantine authorities have stepped up measures to prevent the outbreak of
epidemics of influenza both for humans and animals in South Korea during
the winter season.
A bird flu case was reported in Chunchon, Kangwon Province, raising
concerns over a possible recurrence of avian influenza, although the case
originated from a low-pathogenic virus.
The Ministry of Agriculture and Forestry said Thursday that a total of 20
000 chickens had died of the disease in the city. It has begun quarantine
activities at chicken and duck farmsteads in and around the city.
The ministry has strengthened its vigilance over the epidemic, while also
conducting tests on the secretions of migratory birds in their habitats here.
In the same vein, preventive activities at ports and airports for imports
of livestock products and for travelers from countries with reports of the
virus have been intensified.
The government has also distributed studies on the epidemiological origin
of a high-pathogenic virus of the epidemic to farmsteads and provincial
quarantine authorities.
After acknowledging the need for an international network for global
epidemics, South Korea hosted the 2004 International Conference on Zoonoses
last week, which was the first of its kind in Asia.
[Byline: Bae Keun-min]
